CRITICAL CONCURRENCY FIX v1.8.11: Account variable conflict resolution
🚨 URGENT: Fixed critical variable naming conflict causing NaN capitalAvailable
Root Cause: - Decision.js had both local and global Account variables - Local "Account" was masking global Account instance - This caused capitalAvailable to be NaN in concurrent operations - Result: "❌ [RISK] capitalAvailable inválido: NaN" errors
Solution Implemented: 1. Added missing Account import from '../Backpack/Authenticated/Account.js' 2. Renamed local Account to accountData to prevent naming collision 3. Added Object.assign to sync accountData with global Account 4. Updated getDataset call to use accountData parameter
Changes: - Decision.js: Added Account import, renamed local variable, fixed data flow - Fixed variable scoping issues preventing proper capital calculation - Ensured global Account is always updated with latest data - Resolved "Não foi possível obter capital disponível da conta" errors
This resolves the critical issue where multiple operations failed due to invalid capital calculation caused by variable name conflicts.
🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.ai/code)
Co-Authored-By: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>

FUNDAMENTAL FIX v1.8.9: Proper update logic implementation
🎯 ROOT CAUSE RESOLVED: Fixed fundamental issue with update script logic 🔧 CORRECT BEHAVIOR: Script now replaces ALL GitHub code, preserves ONLY user data 🛡️ SIMPLIFIED: PRESERVE_ITEMS reduced to only user data (.env, src/persistence/) 🚀 FUTURE-PROOF: ANY new GitHub file automatically included in updates
Previous versions tried to selectively preserve code files = guaranteed breakage New logic: Complete src/ replacement + restore only src/persistence/ = bulletproof
Changes: - Removed src/ from PRESERVE_ITEMS (was causing selective update issues) - Replaced updateSrcSelectively() with simple updateSrcDirectory() - Complete src/ removal + GitHub copy + persistence restoration - Removed complex file detection systems (not needed) - Simplified logic: replace everything, preserve only user data
This fixes the fundamental design flaw that caused missing files on updates.
